The paper discusses the word2vec software and its state-of-the-art word embeddings, which are widely used in natural language processing tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the learning models behind the software, which involves neural networks and machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of negative sampling, which is a technique used in neural network training, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of word embeddings in computer vision tasks, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
